The Helios Airways flight ZU522 crashed near Grammatiko, north of Athens, killing all 121 people on board.
Angry relatives demanded answers at Larnaca airport, suspecting a technical fault.
The co-pilot was found slumped over the controls, while the captain was missing.
Experts suggested a loss of cabin pressure led to oxygen deprivation.
Fighter jets shadowed the plane before it crashed, with witnesses describing a chaotic scene.
The cause of the crash remains unclear, but efforts to improve air safety are emphasized.
The tragic event has left many mourning the loss of loved ones.
